#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:6
# 7c5fe3cfdd784505b8c56a63b79941d9
msgid "Salt 0.9.7 Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:8
# 6323dde1954244d38ea8283e60033c4f
msgid "Salt 0.9.7 is here! The latest iteration of Salt brings more features and many fixes. This release is a great refinement over 0.9.6, adding many conveniences under the hood, as well as some features that make working with Salt much better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:13
# 32efe91e1f464ccb8d0c2c728a08bd01
msgid "A few highlights include the new Job system, refinements to the requisite system in states, the ``mod_init`` interface for states, external node classification, search path to managed files in the file state, and refinements and additions to dynamic module loading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:18
# 3bc6854d8f944068a476cb302942c5b4
msgid "0.9.7 also introduces the long developed (and oft changed) unit test framework and the initial unit tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:23
# e40010d0df9a496c82e5c77c730e58ab
msgid "Major Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:26
# 02cbf2474cba4560b1dbc919914d2e65
msgid "Salt Jobs Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:28
# b2f8e774e55847b98a87a1874172d632
msgid "The new jobs interface makes the management of running executions much cleaner and more transparent. Building on the existing execution framework the jobs system allows clear introspection into the active running state of the running Salt interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:33
# c451c089e2d4406c8874849bea498081
msgid "The Jobs interface is centered in the new minion side proc system. The minions now store msgpack serialized files under ``/var/cache/salt/proc``. These files keep track of the active state of processes on the minion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:38
# 2a5df29b44ac4f1db4c5190de03d254c
msgid "Functions in the saltutil Module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:40
# 0df0757d51aa40439a1333c4d1562c35
msgid "A number of functions have been added to the saltutil module to manage and view the jobs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:43
# 0777f694feca4066b44ecc46f05d6ab1
msgid "``running`` - Returns the data of all running jobs that are found in the proc directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:46
# 44f0d4c9f4374a01b1797e374b35aacc
msgid "``find_job`` - Returns specific data about a certain job based on job id."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:48
# 8870ae23cccd41d4996976ddd0c2c3e0
msgid "``signal_job`` - Allows for a given jid to be sent a signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:50
# 92cf76dc16b043fe85543d0767d0a021
msgid "``term_job`` - Sends a termination signal (``SIGTERM, 15``) to the process controlling the specified job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:53
# 8a241eb3f547413186e820c86cbe0674
msgid "``kill_job`` Sends a kill signal (``SIGKILL, 9``) to the process controlling the specified job."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:57
# 70a3b4476c3d468c93ea1a03ef0cc587
msgid "The jobs Runner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:59
# 372d6cf9fae04adda63c31b6890abf5b
msgid "A convenience runner front end and reporting system has been added as well. The jobs runner contains functions to make viewing data easier and cleaner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:62
# b844155afb1a4cc3b692d2896e1945c4
msgid "The jobs runner contains a number of functions..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:65
# 4678c9872ee14bfaa2ad92e90f6709a9
msgid "active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:67
# 73e8f208b8b24f9fa926a264f26f4120
msgid "The active function runs ``saltutil.running`` on all minions and formats the return data about all running jobs in a much more usable and compact format. The active function will also compare jobs that have returned and jobs that are still running, making it easier to see what systems have completed a job and what systems are still being waited on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:74
# 56ac8fdc0fce4940b5abd249649fbba7
msgid "lookup_jid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:76
# 093837b8fcc847d9bc24a4e1c5649d92
msgid "When jobs are executed the return data is sent back to the master and cached. By default is is cached for 24 hours, but this can be configured via the ``keep_jobs`` option in the master configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:80
# 03964ec4022d4d58b4eb5ae76d9d03ba
msgid "Using the ``lookup_jid`` runner will display the same return data that the initial job invocation with the salt command would display."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:84
# 73d63721c8f8402091b027efdd029b68
msgid "list_jobs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:86
# 0ce80c80409e44fcbc938dd4f4dcd1e3
msgid "Before finding a historic job, it may be required to find the job id. ``list_jobs`` will parse the cached execution data and display all of the job data for jobs that have already, or partially returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:92
# d42a5e4eb41b414a9f4ea162eb0fe349
msgid "External Node Classification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:94
# e34f22d7fe584eb19d03cc43e6bbf4c6
msgid "Salt can now use external node classifiers like Cobbler's ``cobbler-ext-nodes``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:97
# 02c1135174984cb7a361c84f10395e2a
msgid "Salt uses specific data from the external node classifier. In particular the classes value denotes which sls modules to run, and the environment value sets to another environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:101
# 0910cb2f1766451aa7cade3491b87846
msgid "An external node classification can be set in the master configuration file via the ``external_nodes`` option: http://salt.readthedocs.org/en/latest/ref/configuration/master.html#external-nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:105
# 0b9b28bcb0884fa49d17713371cf7bdd
msgid "External nodes are loaded in addition to the top files. If it is intended to only use external nodes, do not deploy any top files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:109
# f1d03b2d76a344e684c2a248f96f9ebb
msgid "State Mod Init System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:111
# 2bc9e057ea35488199b5712e29455462
msgid "An issue arose with the pkg state. Every time a package was run Salt would need to refresh the package database. This made systems with slower package metadata refresh speeds much slower to work with. To alleviate this issue the ``mod_init`` interface has been added to salt states."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:116
# 1574e49ea60649c2856a7e19915ee88e
msgid "The ``mod_init`` interface is a function that can be added to a state file. This function is called with the first state called. In the case of the pkg state, the ``mod_init`` function sets up a tag which makes the package database only refresh on the first attempt to install a package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:121
# 2a9a2b6d92bc46838c704c7a8ad13d3c
msgid "In a nutshell, the ``mod_init`` interface allows a state to run any command that only needs to be run once, or can be used to set up an environment for working with the state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:126
# 327854b267704a60a5e5b5316442d9f8
msgid "Source File Search Path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:128
# 53d4769480fc4c469b25932a8ccea019
msgid "The file state continues to be refined, adding speed and capabilities. This release adds the ability to pass a list to the source option. This list is then iterated over until the source file is found, and the first found file is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:132
# 488c979323734124b46ae23820473c26
msgid "The new syntax looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:143
# 35c614a4ec4148a9aaf7ec90dd9fdc16
msgid "The source option can take sources in the list from the salt file server as well as an arbitrary web source. If using an arbitrary web source the checksum needs to be passed as well for file verification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:148
# 47d128972f4b415a87ce6774e692ff37
msgid "Refinements to the Requisite System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:150
# 95d85c937a474f9d8e68cc6ba86a3206
msgid "A few discrepancies were still lingering in the requisite system, in particular, it was not possible to have a ``require`` and a ``watch`` requisite declared in the same state declaration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:154
# 0df091298a044140980e3823c1db5717
msgid "This issue has been alleviated, as well as making the requisite system run more quickly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:158
# 3e4855b95de4481f9c5d3777b4dc464d
msgid "Initial Unit Testing Framework"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:160
# c973369f68c74f90a43a6d0374e568af
msgid "Because of the module system, and the need to test real scenarios, the development of a viable unit testing system has been difficult, but unit testing has finally arrived. Only a small amount of unit testing coverage has been developed, much more coverage will be in place soon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:165
# fa6f40fc6fab4ffc9337df79aedcf657
msgid "A huge thanks goes out to those who have helped with unit testing, and the contributions that have been made to get us where we are. Without these contributions unit tests would still be in the dark."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:170
# b06499f755734046b733d699ebbd741b
msgid "Compound Targets Expanded"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:172
# ef857644f2c749d09411b42a60d3e994
msgid "Originally only support for ``and`` and ``or`` were available in the compound target. 0.9.7 adds the capability to negate compound targets with ``not``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:176
# afc72597926944f682bf9c3fe9244676
msgid "Nodegroups in the Top File"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/releases/0.9.7.rst:178
# 53e6ef223eda4d11a77c11f801f901af
msgid "Previously the nodegroups defined in the master configuration file could not be used to match nodes for states. The nodegroups support has been expanded and the nodegroups defined in the master configuration can now be used to match minions in the top file."
msgstr ""

